First install pygame.
You can do this by running a simple command in the terminal
    for windows users run
        py -m pip install -U pygame --user
    for Mac users run
        python3 -m pip install -U pygame --user
if this does not work for your device see https://www.pygame.org/wiki/GettingStarted 

Download numpy 


When you have neighbors = 4, attribute it the class Twodimensions